<entry valign="top" align="center" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Unit 5: Chapter 9 (1877–1898)</emphasis></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Compelling Question: How did a changing view of government’s responsibility during the Gilded Age affect American society?</emphasis></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry valign="top" align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c2"><emphasis effect="bold">Chapter Objectives:</emphasis>
<list id="fs-idm217866192" list-type="bulleted">
<item>Students will evaluate the consequences of rapid industrialization and the rise of big business on American society and government.</item>
<item>Students will trace the rise of reform movements and how they changed American society and culture.</item>
<item>Students will evaluate the impact of immigration to and migration within the United States during the late nineteenth century.</item></list></entry>
</row>
<row valign="top">
